From: PS4 Linux Baikal Port <noreply@ps4-linux>
Subject: [PATCH] mt76x8: port to cfg80211 / fs API in Linux 6.15+

Bring the 2018-vintage MediaTek MT7668 vendor driver forward to compile
against Linux 6.15.4. The driver still targets the kernel 5.4-era cfg80211
and VFS APIs; this patch is the mechanical wire-up to the modern surfaces.

Changes are split per call site, each behind a LINUX_VERSION_CODE guard so
the driver still builds against older trees:

  - platform.c, gl_kal.c: replace get_fs/set_fs/mm_segment_t + f_op->{read,write}
    file I/O with kernel_read/kernel_write (the in-kernel fs-segment dance was
    removed in 5.18).
  - gl_kal.c: drop netif_rx_ni() in favour of netif_rx() (removed in 5.18,
    netif_rx() is now safe in any context).
  - gl_kal.c: rename del_timer_sync() -> timer_delete_sync() (renamed in 6.2).
  - gl_kal.c: cfg80211_roam_info channel/bssid moved into links[0] for MLO.
  - gl_kal.c: drop the struct module* argument from
    kallsyms_on_each_symbol() callback (signature changed in 6.0).
  - gl_kal.h: include <linux/sched/clock.h> for local_clock().
  - gl_init.c: drop MODULE_SUPPORTED_DEVICE() (removed in 5.16+).
  - gl_init.c: rename del_timer_sync() -> timer_delete_sync().
  - gl_init.c, gl_p2p.c: cfg80211_ops callbacks grew "unsigned int link_id"
    (or "int link_id") parameters for MLO; add thin adapter wrappers so the
    static vendor functions match the new struct cfg80211_ops signatures
    without rewriting them. Affected callbacks: add_key, get_key, del_key,
    set_default_key, set_default_mgmt_key, tdls_mgmt, change_beacon,
    stop_ap, set_bitrate_mask, get_tx_power, start_radar_detection,
    set_tx_power, set_wiphy_params.
  - gl_p2p.c: cfg80211_ap_update wraps cfg80211_beacon_data; change_beacon
    adapter unwraps the embedded beacon.
  - gl_cfg80211.c: cfg80211_scan_request::scan_width was retired with 802.11n;
    skip the field on 6.7+.
  - gl_cfg80211.c: station_parameters::{supported_rates,ht_capa,vht_capa}
    moved into link_sta_params. A STA_PARAMS_LINK(p) macro hides the
    difference at each access.
  - gl_p2p_kal.c: wireless_dev::cac_started moved to links[0].cac_started in
    6.0; cfg80211_cac_event() gained a link_id parameter in 6.5.
  - p2p_func.c: cfg80211_ch_switch_notify() gained a link_id parameter in
    6.3.
  - common/wlan_oid.c: replace userspace <stddef.h> with <linux/stddef.h>.
  - mt76x8/Kconfig, drv_wlan/Kconfig: declare bool instead of tristate so
    the driver can be linked into vmlinux (required for PS4 boot where the
    rootfs has no module loader for early WiFi bring-up).

Builds clean with CONFIG_MT76X8=y, CONFIG_MT6632=y, and CONFIG_CFG80211=y
on Linux 6.15.4. Only warnings remain (missing prototypes, mostly
pre-existing in the vendor tree).
